smtAssociationID.name: smtAssociationID
smtAssociationID.description: The Association ID of an association between an Access Point and a Station. The size constraint is taken from IEEE 802.11 section 7.3.1.8. For an Access Point, this object is always zero.

smtCapabilityInfo.name: smtCapabilityInfo
smtCapabilityInfo.description: The Capability Information of this entity.

smtPowerSaveInterval.name: smtPowerSaveInterval
smtPowerSaveInterval.description: The time limit, in units of beacon intervals, after which the Client will go into Power Save Mode if the Client does not detect activity. For an Access Point, this object is always zero.

smtListenInterval.name: smtListenInterval
smtListenInterval.description: The time, in units of beacon intervals, that may pass before the Client awakens and listens for the next Beacon. For an Access Point, this object is always zero.

smtATIMWindow.name: smtATIMWindow
smtATIMWindow.description: The duration of the ATIM Window, in TUs. For an Access Point, this object is always zero.

smtOperationalChannels.name: smtOperationalChannels
smtOperationalChannels.description: The list of DS channels that shall be scanned with a higher priority. All channels allowed by the current regulatory domain are scanned, the channels specified in this object are visited more frequently compared to the channels not in the set of this object. If the object is null, the PHY will default to the channel configured by dot11CurrentChannel.

smtCurrentBSSID.name: smtCurrentBSSID
smtCurrentBSSID.description: The current Basic Service Set ID. For a Client, this object either contains the BSSID of the Access Point with which the Client is associated or the BSSID of the IBSS it is currently participating in (smtCurrentBSSType indicates which of the two cases holds). If the object is all zeros, the Client is not associated or participating in an IBSS. For an Access Point, this object contains the BSSID of the Access Point. If the Access Point is in the process of resetting, the object is all zeros.

smtCurrentSSID.name: smtCurrentSSID
smtCurrentSSID.description: The current Service Set ID. For a Client, this object either contains the SSID of the infrastructure network or the SSID of the IBSS it currently associated with or participating in. For an Access Point, this object contains the BSSID of the Access Point. If the Access Point is resetting, the object is null.

smtCurrentBSSType.name: smtCurrentBSSType
smtCurrentBSSType.description: The type of the Basic Service Set. For a Client, this object indicates the type of SS it currently is associated with, participating in. For an Access Point, this object is 1 (infrastructure).

smtPublicKeyEnable.name: smtPublicKeyEnable
smtPublicKeyEnable.description: This object specifies whether public-key techniques shall be used to negotiate keys.

smtQualityLevel0.name: smtQualityLevel0
smtQualityLevel0.description: This object relates quality level to a transmission rate. Level 0 specifies the lowest (basic) rate.

smtQualityLevel1.name: smtQualityLevel1
smtQualityLevel1.description: This object relates quality level to a transmission rate. Level 1 specifies the second lowest (basic) rate.

smtQualityLevel2.name: smtQualityLevel2
smtQualityLevel2.description: This object relates quality level to a transmission rate. Level 2 specifies the an arbitrary (higher) rate.

smtQualityPenalty.name: smtQualityPenalty
smtQualityPenalty.description: This object specifies a quality penalty for transmission failures.

smtStationDBTimeout.name: smtStationDBTimeout
smtStationDBTimeout.description: This object specifies a timeout on entries and their state information in the Station database. For Clients the Station database is mapped on the roamTable. For Access Points, the Station database is mapped on the assocTable. The timeout is in seconds.

smtQualityIndicator.name: smtQualityIndicator
smtQualityIndicator.description: This object selects the quality indicator from the baseband. Current quality indicators are: 1 = Signal Quality 1 (SQ1) 2 = Signal Quality 2 (SQ2) 3 = Signal Quality 3 (SQ3)

smtQualityUpperLimit.name: smtQualityUpperLimit
smtQualityUpperLimit.description: An upper limit for the quality.

smtQualityLowerLimit.name: smtQualityLowerLimit
smtQualityLowerLimit.description: A lower limit for the quality.

smtCWMin.name: smtCWMin
smtCWMin.description: The CWMin value as defined by IEEE 802.11. Needs to be a power of 2, minus 1.

smtCWMax.name: smtCWMax
smtCWMax.description: The CWMax value as defined by IEEE 802.11. Needs to be a power of 2, minus 1, larger than or equal to smtCWMin.

smtACKWindow.name: smtACKWindow
smtACKWindow.description: The ACK frame time out defined in number of slottimes. This can be used to optimize long range links.

assocTableMaxLength.name: assocTableMaxLength
assocTableMaxLength.description: This object specifies the maximum number of associations the assocTable can hold.

assocTable.name: assocTable
assocTable.description: The Association table. This table contains all the Clients associated with the Access Point. The index of the entry equals the Association ID of the Client with the Access Point. An entry in the table is only valid if the assocAddress object of that entry contains a MAC address other then the all zeros MAC address. Refer to sections 5.7 and 11.3 of the 802.11 standard for more information on associations. The table is read-only.

assocEntry.name: assocEntry
assocEntry.description: An entry in the Association Table.

assocIndex.name: assocIndex
assocIndex.description: The index into the association table. The index equals the association ID that is in use for the Client.

assocAddress.name: assocAddress
assocAddress.description: MAC address of a Client associated with the Access Point. If the association is pending (that is, the Client is scanning, authenticating or associating), assocAddress contains the MAC address of that Client with the group bit set to indicate that the Access Point is aware of the presence of that Client. The other objects of the entry will be updated based on the information extracted from the received Probe Requests.

assocQuality.name: assocQuality
assocQuality.description: An indicator for the quality of the Client. If the association is still pending, the quality is calculated over the received Probe Requests from the Client. If the Client is associated, the quality derived from any activity with the Client. The actual quality source depends on the selected quality indicator. The semantics of the indicator is 'low is good quality' and 'high is bad quality'.

assocAge.name: assocAge
assocAge.description: An indicator (in seconds) for the age of the information on the Client. The age is reset to 0 if any activity of this Client is detected.

assocRSSI.name: assocRSSI
assocRSSI.description: An indicator for the RSSI of the Client. If the association is still pending, the RSSI is calculated over the received Probe Requests from the Client. If the Client is associated, the RSSI derived from any activity with the Client.

secMACAclMaxTableLength.name: secMACAclMaxTableLength
secMACAclMaxTableLength.description: The maximum number of entries that the secMACAclTable can contain.

secMACAclTable.name: secMACAclTable
secMACAclTable.description: The table containing an access control list (acl) with MAC addresses of 802.11 Clients and whether they are allowed to communicate with the wireless network through this Access Point. This table enforces a source address check. An address of FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF is used as a default entry, i.e., it determines the access control for Clients that are otherwise not listed in this table. When the table is empty, every Client is denied.

secMACAclAddress.name: secMACAclAddress
secMACAclAddress.description: The MAC address of a Client allowed to join the network through this Access Point. The address FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF constitutes the default behaviour for addresses not contained in this table.

secMACAclAllowed.name: secMACAclAllowed
secMACAclAllowed.description: The flag indicating whether the corresponding MAC address is allowed to communicate through this Access Point or not.

secMACAclRowStatus.name: secMACAclRowStatus
secMACAclRowStatus.description: The status value for creating and deleting rows in this table.

secLastError.name: secLastError
secLastError.description: When a security violation or error occurs, the error code is written to this variable in the form of a string.

secLastErrorAddress.name: secLastErrorAddress
secLastErrorAddress.description: When a security violation or error occurs, the MAC address involved in the violation or error is written to this variable.

securityViolation.name: securityViolation
securityViolation.description: A security violation was detected. The secLastErrorCode indicates the type of error/violation, the secLastErrorAddress indicates the involved MAC address.

roamScanType.name: roamScanType
roamScanType.description: This object configures the type of scanning the Client uses.

roamScanInterval.name: roamScanInterval
roamScanInterval.description: The interval, in units of beacon intervals, between successive scans during an association.

roamProbeDelay.name: roamProbeDelay
roamProbeDelay.description: This object specifies the delay (in ms) to be used prior to transmitting a Probe frame during active scanning. The object implements the ProbeDelay parameter of the MLME-SCAN.request primitive as defined in section 10.3.2.1 of the 802.11 standard.

roamMinChannelTime.name: roamMinChannelTime
roamMinChannelTime.description: This object specifies the minimum time (in time units) to spend on each channel when scanning. The object implements the MinChannelTime parameter in the MLME-SCAN.request primitive as defined in section 10.3.2.1 of the 802.11 standard.

roamMaxChannelTime.name: roamMaxChannelTime
roamMaxChannelTime.description: This object specifies the maximum time (in time units) to spend on each channel when scanning. The object implements the MaxChannelTime parameter in the MLME-SCAN.request primitive as defined in section 10.3.2.1 of the 802.11 standard.

roamJoinTimeout.name: roamJoinTimeout
roamJoinTimeout.description: The firmware will keep trying to find a suitable BSS until another MLME-JOIN.request is issued. The object roamJoinTimeout allows the application to estimate how long it at least has to wait before it can assume that MLME-JOIN.request is likely to fail. The object should be considered for information purposes. Changing the object will have no effect. Future versions may use this object to limit the time it spends to try to join a specific Service Set.

roamBeaconPeriodTimeout.name: roamBeaconPeriodTimeout
roamBeaconPeriodTimeout.description: The time limit, in units of beacon intervals, after which the association is voided if no beacons are received.

roamDontSwitch.name: roamDontSwitch
roamDontSwitch.description: The time limit, in units of beacon intervals, during which the Client will not use BSS quality parameters for making the roaming decissions if it becomes associated with an Access Point.

roamBlackout.name: roamBlackout
roamBlackout.description: The time, in units of beacon intervals, during which the BSS is not considered candidate after the association was denied or voided.

roamDisassociateTime.name: roamDisassociateTime
roamDisassociateTime.description: The time, in units of beacon intervals, taken by the Disassociate procedure.

roamHandoffTime.name: roamHandoffTime
roamHandoffTime.description: Time, in time units, during which data to the Access Point is hold before a handoff is performed.

roamWeightMetric1.name: roamWeightMetric1
roamWeightMetric1.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric2.name: roamWeightMetric2
roamWeightMetric2.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric3.name: roamWeightMetric3
roamWeightMetric3.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric4.name: roamWeightMetric4
roamWeightMetric4.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric5.name: roamWeightMetric5
roamWeightMetric5.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric6.name: roamWeightMetric6
roamWeightMetric6.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric7.name: roamWeightMetric7
roamWeightMetric7.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamWeightMetric8.name: roamWeightMetric8
roamWeightMetric8.description: A metric used to make roaming decisions.

roamTableLength.name: roamTableLength
roamTableLength.description: This object specifies the maximum number of entries the roamTable can hold.

roamTable.name: roamTable
roamTable.description: The Roaming table contains all the BSSs the Client is aware of. An entry in the roamTable is only valid if the roamBSSID object of that entry contains a MAC address other then the all zeros MAC address. The table implements the BSSDescription table as defined in 10.3.2.2 of the 802.11 standard. This table is read-only.

roamEntry.name: roamEntry
roamEntry.description: An entry in the Roaming table.

roamBSSID.name: roamBSSID
roamBSSID.description: The BSSID of the BSS. If this entry in the roamTable is not used, the roamBSSID is all zeros.

roamSSID.name: roamSSID
roamSSID.description: The Service Set ID the BSS is part of.

roamBSSType.name: roamBSSType
roamBSSType.description: The BSS Type of the entry.

roamChannel.name: roamChannel
roamChannel.description: The DS channel the BSS is using.

roamAge.name: roamAge
roamAge.description: An indicator (in seconds) for the age of the information on the BSS. The age is reset to 0 if a Beacon of this BSS is received.

roamQuality.name: roamQuality
roamQuality.description: An indicator for the quality of the BSS. The quality is calculated over the received Beacons of the BSS and depends on the selected quality indicator. The semantics of the indicator is 'low is good quality' and 'high is bad quality'.

roamLoad.name: roamLoad
roamLoad.description: An indicator for the load of the BSS.

roamBeaconPeriod.name: roamBeaconPeriod
roamBeaconPeriod.description: The beacon period (in time units) of this BSS.

roamDTIMPeriod.name: roamDTIMPeriod
roamDTIMPeriod.description: The DTIM period of this BSS.

roamCapabilityInfo.name: roamCapabilityInfo
roamCapabilityInfo.description: The Capability Information for this BSS.

roamRates.name: roamRates
roamRates.description: The bit rates supported by the BSS. The least-significant 7 bits of each non-null octet value are a count from 00h -7Fh, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kbit/s. The most-significant bit of each non-null octet is set to one if the data rate represented by this octet is a member of the basic rate set and is set to zero if this data rate is optional. The list ends with a null octet.

roamRSSI.name: roamRSSI
roamRSSI.description: An indicator for the RSSI of the BSS. The RSSI is calculated over the received Beacons of the BSS.

smtGroup.name: smtGroup
smtGroup.description: The additional objects for Station Management

dot11ExtBasicCompl.description: The implementation requirements for an IEEE 802.11 Station.
